{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, shaping rewards can help to gradually shift an algorithm's focus towards more complex or unexpected outcomes.",
    "Incorporating other motivation-like mechanisms indirectly through novel loss functions, regularization methods, or (e.g., curiosity-driven) training strategies can encourage diversity and exploration.",
    "These approaches are what afford these systems their unprecedented potential to expand the frontiers of human knowledge and creativity.",
    "However, the drive to outwardly expand human knowledge lies in direct contradiction to the impulse that underlies personalization, which is to narrowly channel information in line with existing inclinations.",
    "AI policies should actively promote the capacity of AI systems to help humans critically reflect, evaluate and act on information in new ways, not according to the old ways."
  ]
}